folder: Lafayette Avenue & Washington Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Lafayette Avenue, north side, east from Washington Avenue. The corner building is an old Friends Meeting House as shown on Atlases from 1880. The low building on its right is a Baptist Sunday school and next to it is the Emanuel Baptist Church, at the N.W. corner of St. James Place. At the N.E. corner is the St. dames Protestant Episcopel Church (triangular front).
P. L. Sperr  View 1: July 22, 1934
NO REpRODUCTIONS  View 2: October 12, 1940
